,Recommended,270550,12702428,"Posted: 30 October, 2014",all,Roland Deschain,"This game is a great arcade-esque style shoot em' up and I adore it. I played for a few hours with a friend and it was a lot of fun but I have a few suggestions to improve gameplay:1. SKILLS-You can put a point after every round into a skill-Skills could be like: accuracy, damage, run speed. and scavenger (get more from cash/supply drops)2. GUN UPGRADES-Pay to get various upgrades/attatchments to your guns-Such as: incendiary (does dmg over time) explosive (hurts more than one target) or like an increase in damage, accuracy or firing speed3.CHARACTERS-We need just a little bit of character development, who is ""The Girl""? Or ""The SWAT""?-I suggest adding MORE characters and giving them each starting attributes depending on who they are like: The SWAT gets a defense bonus due to his bulletproof vest.4.TRAPS-You should add more traps and trap like elements to the game-Such as a bear trap that costs, say, $50 and you could put them in a 1/4 space of a normal tile-Fire traps would be cool5.PALISADES-Palisades should decay with damage and you should have to pay to repair them-The advantage of this would be you could add in palisade damage. As in they do damage to zombies based on how new and freshly repaired they are.These are just a few suggestions that I thought could make this game better, even though it already is pretty addicting.-ZacP.S. Add some detail to the map, just a few cracks in the concrete or litter. Something to make it more immersive.EDIT: Nearly a year later, I played this game again and saw that the devs practically took all my ideas and implemented them and I couldn't be happier! Skills and traps have been added and so have harmful palisades! They also added a couple of aesthetic details to the map! Awesome work guys and thanks for using my ideas :D"
