,Recommended,270550,13679638,"Posted: 28 December, 2014",all,A String's Vibrato (Violoncello),"Within the time I've played this game, it helps pass the time. It's like a basic tycoon game in which you can earn money as you kill zombies. As you progress, the zombies become stronger and more lethal. Trying to survive 10 nights might seem difficult enough, but getting at any point past night 10 is difficult if you have less than four people. Trying to get all the achievements can be a challenge and makes more goals to go after in this game. What I liked most about this game is the accessibility to auto-turrents and the ability to mount any weapon on top of them, making them fierce allies if you're able to protect them. My personal favorite weapon is the Telsa Ray, which can attack up to three zombies at once, and is basically an instant-kill gun. I love the idea of ammo sharing and whenever some gains a health pack you get some of it too. It was definitely worth the $0.69 I paid for. Even though I currently only have 2.6 hours on it, I expect to add more, seeing a this is an enjoyable game to play.Some things to know before you play:You can have up to 4 people playing with you.You can customize your server to personnal or to publicThe game becomes harder as you playIt matters where you place everythingThe Rocket Launcher is not a good gunThe auto turrents are VERY usefulAt random nights, there are sales on various item in the storeNever play aloneThe street light is your friendSome thing that could be added:Better assortment of weaponsNew barricadesPossibly new mapsNew charactersNew game mode (Example: A defending mode where you have to protect the street lamp from the zombies.)Few various tweaks on the AIs of the zombiesVoice chat in the gameAnd maybe a few bosses that come out each night during the horde, to add a little spice to the game!I hope this helped you and gave you a proper decision on whether to buy this game or not, but I will say this; It is defininetly worth the amount of money it is being sold for, very fun and low graphics, meaning you can have a fast gameplay on slow laptops, like mine! Enjoy the game!"
