,Not Recommended,270550,12154203,"Posted: 19 September, 2014",all,Argyraspides,"So, let's define what a typical video game zombie horde is:1) Dumb as a rock2) Highly predictable3) Extremely numerous4) Individually fragileFrankly, this game's biggest failure is that, instead of just making the zomibes more numerous, which would make sense, they make them individually stronger AND more numerous. Hey, kids, want to play a game where each of the 60 on-screen zombies take a whole assault rifle clip to kill? Where the basic weapons are vastly more effective than the advanced ones? Well, you're in luck, because this game exists.In a nutshell: If you're looking for something to tie into a drinking game at your next LAN party, you might get a few kicks from this. Otherwise, you're looking at 20-30 minutes of entertainment for your 2$. It could be fun with weaker zombies, and with more weapons and features, but if you just -really- need your zombie survival fix, go play Unturned instead."
