76561198033802030,Recommended,270550,19348269,"Posted: 28 November, 2015",all,sudo sandwich,"Summary: Inexpensive twin-stick overhead defense.Multiplayer: 4 Online Co-opCompletion: Never ends, but death is likely within 1 hour.Cards: YesCloud: NoYet Another Zombie Defense is as its name implies. It's an overhead twin-stick shooter game where you spend each day shooting zombies who seem to have an uncanny knack for knowing where you are. The game plays on a single, large parking lot with a lone street lamp to keep you company as you gun down masses of ever-increasing zombies who become faster, stronger, and more durable with each passing day. Killing zombies provides you with funds with which to buy new guns, ammo, turrets, and fences (Who's selling these? Ah who cares).The graphics are serviceable. They look like they were designed with the bare minimum. I haven't experienecd any slowdown, so that's a good sign. Collision detection is a little spotty, as it can be hard to tell when you get hit, and fences act a bit weird on how you can walk past them. As for the music, I hope you like combat and build phase songs because those are the only two songs you will ever hear. They're not bad, but you will almost certainly want to put on some other tunes after you've heard them a few times.Endless mode is a nice change of pace for when you get tired of the same gameplay. In it, you cannot purchase anything and must make do with random drops provided by the zombies. It's all kiting the old-fashioned way. Overall the standard game is much more satisfying to play though.The best way to enjoy this game by far is with friends. This game was meant for co-op survival and to that end it does it very well. No matter how good you are you're going to die, as the zombies scale much faster than you. Your cash reserves are pooled together, so it's best to play with someone you can trust, as sometimes strangers are unaware of this fact and spend your cash by accident.So the big question is, is it worth it? Yup, this is one game I can recommend even at full price, just because of how inexpensive it is. The return value in entertainment is quite good, and having friends to play it with makes it all the better. Surprisingly YAZD is updated from time to time, so it can be worth coming back to after a long hiatus to find out what's new.  I rate this game a 8.5/10 for its nice combination of affordability, multiplayer, and fun."
