,Recommended,270550,13795931,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,SON1XX,"I bought this game because I had a 90% off coupon at the time, bringing it down to a lowly 16p (£ - Currency) which is the cheapest I've ever paid for a game. If I'm honest I wasn't expecting much for the mere pittance I was spending here. Regardless whether you have a money off coupon or not for this game hardly changes the fact you should still buy this game. It's fun, and I mean stupidly fun. For something so simple, so basic, it's survival at it's finest. There are no tricks, but challenges. You can try it alone or you can team up with your friends to see how many waves of the undead you can repel, whilst earning cash drops for weapon upgrades, ammo resuply, defences, and other accessories. The zombies get tougher and faster as each wave begins so some sort of strategy might be in order. Do you run circles around them, or do you just hide behind  you defences? The agony of choice. Both have merits. Both have flaws.Soon you will be zombie nom nom."
