,Recommended,270550,23108174,"Posted: 20 May, 2016",all,TRU±PlayMaker,"IntroductionYet Another Zombie Defense is a game which puts players versus zombies in a fight for survival on a very simple map. It's a very simple and straightforward top-down, arcadey shooter with a fairly large arsenal of weapons and defensive options to be used. There is a lot of fun to be had with this one, and has some very interesting stategic options to fit many playstyles. Read further to learn more.GameplayThe gameplay of YAZD (I'll refer to it by this acronym) is divided into three sections: Classic, Survival and Deathmatch. One common thing between these three is that the zombies get stronger and stronger over time, which means that no matter how hard you try, you're eventually going to die at some point though you can hold out for pretty long especially with a full 4-man squad. Speaking of which, this game supports a maximum of 4 players in any multiplayer game. Zombies drop ammo, money and power-ups for the player randomly when killed.ClassicYour goal is to survive each night from a horde of zombies that spawn. Each night has more zombies, and their defensive, offensive and mobility multipliers go higher every night meaning that survival is less and less likely each night. To your aid are weapons, pickups and the store. After you complete a night, you can shop from the store which randomly has items on sale. Money is an important resource which you collect from dead zombies, and can be the difference between an impenetrable defense and a failed run.Every few nights you get a skill point which can be allocated to upgrade one of the following: Movement speed, pickup range, health regeneration, health points or reload speed. It's important to identify which particular upgrade path suits your playstyle and stick to it. Survive long enough and you'll get to upgrade them all, but some upgrades are better than others early on.Defensive and Offensive options are plentiful and really cater to multiple strategic playstyles. Want to run around shooting zombies that chase you? Grab an automatic weapon like the uzi. Prefer to snipe out entire lines of enemies? Sniper Rifle. Need an effective area of effect weapon? Grab a rocket launcher or the tesla coil. The combinations are endless, but your money and ammo is not, so always think ahead.SurvivalThis time it's a race against the clock to see how long you can hold out from the endless wave of zombies chasing you. There is no shop here so the only thing that drops are weapons. Good luck collecting them though.DeathmatchI haven't played this one enough to give it a detailed review, but essentially you can now hurt other players whilst having to deal with zombies at the same time. I will update soon.VisualsYAZD doesn't really have much in the graphics department. It's not horrible on the eyes, but it's not very good either. The one map it has is very plain, and the edges of the map are simply black. A lot more could be done visually to give it a better feeling overall, but the devs may not go that direction.AudioThe soundtrack, while being okay, is repetitive and limited. Again, not much worth mentioning here.Summary & ConclusionYAZD is best played with your friends or anyone online for that matter. The fight for survival is a very fun experience, and can lead to some rather tense moments where you're struggling to keep your base from falling as the zombies close in. Playing solo is not really recommended, as there's much less zombie killing action to really enjoy, but you can if you want to. At the price it's easy to pick up and play, and it goes on sale quite often, so it's definitely worth your time and money. For what this game offers at its price:7/10 -Must...Survive...Another...NightIf you found this review helpful, please consider giving it a thumbs up. You can also find more reviews over athttp://www.completingthebackloggroup.com/Please also check out Completing the Backlog's Curator pagehere- follow for regular updates on reviews for other games!"
