,Recommended,270550,18319797,"Posted: 3 October, 2015",all,Paraturtle,"I will rate the two primary factors to this game (Gameplay and Sound) and include a final score below.__________________________________________-Gameplay 8/10 (Very Good)The premise of the game is to survive wave after wave of zombies that increase in Toughness (health), Damage, and Speed. Each kill you earn is money in your pocket, and they regularly drop pick-ups from ammo, limited power-ups, and bonus cash. After each wave you have the chance to build barricades, guns, or turrets to mount guns. After a certain amount of kills, the player can choose from a tier list of upgrades including but not limited to: Reload Speed, Run Speed, Health Regen. After beating a minimum of 7 waves, the player can now play endless night mode in which the entire game is spent during the zombie phase and you progress by picking up weapons the zombies drop and pray to God you won't die.The difficulty in this game is incredibly high. Getting passed early waves is easy but your choice in purchases will impact how far you can get in the long wrong. There's a limit to the amount of money you can make each round, and it's up to RNG to decide how many drops of bonus cash you can get to help buy those extra barricades or that final turret. The micromanagement of your cash is probably the most engaging part of the game, but as most defence games work this way this becomes an incredibly fun part about the game. Zombies have a one track mind and will do everything they can to get their hands on you, and their spawns are quite methodical as they will appear to surround you within a second with only one way out. It's very bullet-hell-ish.The Multiplayer aspect of the game is spot-on and has virtually no issues other than minor connectivity problems that seldom appear.-Sound 5/10 (Average)The audio in this game is quite cheap. The song that plays on loop is bland, landing itself on the sweet spot of, ""This is a constant loop but it's not annoying so I can tune it out white noise."" The weapon sounds feel like an after thought, like the developers forgot that they needed sound the entire time and made quick sounds, leveled them so they weren't abnoxiously loud, and then released the product a little early. However, like the music, they're on a sweet spot of comfortable absence.FINAL SCORE........... 7/10 (Good)__________________________________________Rating System:10 - Fantastic9 - Great8 - Very Good7 - Good6 - Fine5 - Average4 - Bad3 - Very Bad2 - Horrible1 - Apalling"
