76561198060783091,Recommended,270550,17752621,"Posted: 28 August, 2015",all,Shibbles,"Pew pew! DIE ZOMBIE DIE!A very good game for such a cheap price, some features are missing but I couldn't complain because this is a small indie game.So you're thrown into the game straight away there's no story it's simply just a survival game with the object being either survive as many nights as you possibly can by building up your fort with the money you earn from killing zombies and picking up loot drops, or to try out the gamemode ""Endless Night"" where you never stop fighting zombies!Features:- The game ran smoothly with lots of events and animations happening.- The achievements to unlock make the game more challenging!- Multiplayer can be setup very easily for either friends only to join you or for you to let anyone looking to play online join you in on your game.- Zombie difficulty scales up each night.- The odd chance a zombie could drop a bonus timed boost for you.- There's a RPG leveling system for certain player skills (more playstyles).- Controls for both controller and mouse and keyboard.Missing Features:- Customizable characters.- Different types of zombies.- A few public servers where everyone could connect and play (no private match servers).- Players inventorys/weapons were independant in multiplayer not the hosts inventory.- Some different maps, random maps maybe?Another than that I really like the game and I would suggest it if you're looking for something to kill time with either on your own or with a friend, well worth the cheap price!"
