,Recommended,270550,21245610,"Posted: 15 February, 2016",all,Emperor Eagle,"Firstly I saw this game for an ultra cheap price during the Steam sales.  Then I looked and saw that a few of my friends had it too.  So I bought it thinking that if the game was bad I wasn't going to be very disappointed because of the cheap price.  I downloaded it and realised that it hardly took up any space, that was good.  Or was it bad, small games are often bad.  No, no, this game was great.  I launched it immediately (sort of, a day or two after I bought it, so not really immediately) and the game loaded within seconds.  It came up with a menu full of zombies that were ready to kill you and eat your brains as soon as they saw you.I pushed play.  It was a single player game as I wanted to have a go by myself before I went co-op with others.  Once you press play there are a series of options.  They are the choices of a character ('The Guy', 'The Girl' and 'The SWAT), a game mode (defence, endless night and death match) and the types of players that could join (everyone, friends only and local).  The controls were easy to master and the first couple of nights were pretty simple.  Soon enough I had a few achievements that were super easy to earn.  That's one good thing about this game.  There are easy, medium and hard achievements to earn, all of them will take time but none of them are out of the range of a medium skilled zombie slayer.In Yet Another Zombie Defence I found almost nothing to criticise.  Apart from the facts that some of the settings don't change much like the blood for example.  One hundred percent means you have heaps of blood flying everywhere and spattering on the ground making a mess.  If the blood is on zero percent you will still have heaps of blood flying everywhere and spattering on the ground making a mess.  There is also the problem of being able to walk through some of the barricades but not others in between levels.Anyway, for all of these reasons stated in the many paragraphs I would rate Yet Another Zombie Defence 91/100 for its fun cooperative gameplay and for its easy to use set up (the menu, the default controls and the item shop setups).  It could have better graphics but for the type of game it is, they wouldn't need to be much better.  It is a brilliant game that I would recommend to anyone who likes shooting, strategy and zombie survival games.  Great game."
