76561198072672842,Recommended,270550,16779509,"Posted: 29 June, 2015",all,76561193777705546,"Actually YAZD is a pretty good game. Now, this is being said in consideration that this is anindiegame, meaining it won't have as good graphics, it may not have original sounds or even soundtracks, and it just overall won't be that one game you always play (sometimes). YAZD however, does not in my opinion fall into the last critique.The gameplay, the bread of the entire indie sandwich, is very straightforward and easy to get used to. You move around with (for gamepad users) the left stick, shoot with right trigger, and aim with right stick. Aiming is pretty on point and you hit your target 98 times out of 100.The sounds should be split into two categories: sound effects and soundtracks. The sound effects are okay, not too many of them and the ones that are there aren't the best, but keep in mind that this is an inide game, right? The actual soundtracks, the music playing as you zombie defend, is the same one every round. While in the main menu and in daytime there is a second soundtrack, but it's kind of corny with the same ""Darkness... is coming..."" opreatic repeated over and over.There is no dlc for this game, meaning when you buy it for $1.99 (or 49 cents, the price i got on sale) you're buying the whole thing. You won't need to drop another 30 dollars on in game currency or costumes of maps - which, and i need to say this, there is only one map, for day and night time. It's a concrete lot with a single street light in the middle.All in all you won't really be wasting your money on this game. It's very addictive and fun to play with friends, especially those who enjoy zombie defense games. It runs very well on a computer like mine, which has an okay graphics card and a processor with two CPUs. YAZD is not the finest game of it's kind, but it's still a fun and worth it's price (even more for sale price) game to grab any day. Get a two pack next time you see it on sale and enjoy it with your best friend :P"
