76561198124807763,Recommended,270550,25496703,"Posted: 13 September, 2016",all,Hugh Mungus,"I bought 4 copies of this game, one for myself and 3 for my friends. I got it a couple months back for 49 cents each. Every cent was worth it. One of the most fun games to play with your friends. Just mess around and shoot zombies for a while. What's even better, my friends would troll each other by making a massive hoard chase around one guy, which in the end, he would get surrounded and mauled to death. Hilarious. The gameplay may not be amazing, but the laughs you will get will be worth it. However, I would like to warn people; DO NOT BUY FOR FULL PRICE! The game may be fun to play with friends, but it isn't worth a cent over 49. Here's why:Pros:A lot of fun with friends.Zombie mechanics and gun mechanics make for funny gameplay.Forts are fun to build and get trapped in, and be laughed at by your friends.Very well optimized and absolutely zero bugs.Very easy to connect with friends.Cons:Very amateur.Not fun in solo.Extremely rare updates.I highly recommend Skype for playing with friends (when they are at their homes), it just makes the experience better.Overall, 10/10.P.S. I will be buying more copies of the game if the price drops below 49 cents during a sale."
