,Recommended,270550,10207792,"Posted: 23 May, 2014",all,OppositeOfGod,"I've read the negative reviews, and I understand them completely. This is a very basic game. Just point and click. Hell, you don't even have to keep clicking, you just need to hold down the left mouse button and watch devestation unfold. However, I recommend this game for two reasons. 1.) It's only 2 dollars. It costs less than most games on your cell phone. 2.) It's nostalgic. I don't remember how many times, be it in high school or even college, that I would play certain tower defense games that just involved pointing and clicking. (Hover over enemy, click them X number of times and watch them die) I love games like that. They are simple, to the point, and can bring hours of fun. Not to mention that you can play this game ONLINE with your friends or with anyone else who just happens to be on the game.True, there aren't too many weapons right now and it's also true that after you hit a million points it just sort of gets repetitive. But hey, what do you expect from something that costs less than a soda? This is one of those games that has many options for future developement. I really look forward to new weapons, new enemies, who knows what else might come. Also, one more perk about this game. It's a very small install size. It downloads fast and installs fast; and you don't need to worry about it soaking up your space like other games do."
