,Recommended,270550,12756500,"Posted: 2 November, 2014",all,Mr.VIPGuest,"I bought this game as part of the Holloween special- and for 49 cents, it was a steal. Seriously. You can pay for this with a few trading cards.~~Anyways, let me get into the actual review.~~The game is simple enough, and as you might expect, it is light on content. But the fact that it costs less than the average IOS or Android game makes it worth purchasing if you have some change just sitting in your steam account.As of this review the game has two modes. Endless night, which is literally just a test of will to see how long you can last without any defenses, and the normal game mode. In the latter, you have access to traps, weapons, and barricades you can purchase after each night ends. Similar to Call of Duty zombies, each wave gets increasingly harder, but also awards to player with health, ammo, and money drops. All are very important to survival, and without them you would be dead meat in minutes.And well, that['s pretty much it. If this game was more than a couple bucks, I would give it a bad review. But the fact that it was so cheap leads me to say that if you just want a quick game to play to satisfy your zombie needs, you should definitely pick it up.Finally, I just want to say that the developer has mentioned free updates in the future, and while I look foward to seeing them, it appears they come very slowly, as the last update was 2 months ago."
