76561197994190157,Recommended,270550,33597642,Posted: 16 July,all,A Guy on a Buffalo,"Zombies? Check.Easy to learn? Check.Fun with friends? Check.Fast game? Check.Cheap? Check.Quick download? Check.This game is really fun. The achievements are difficult (but not impossible) to earn, and some of them you have to make a conscious effort to attain, which I definitely like. Played this originally at a LAN night with friends. The only downside in my opinion is that it only fits 4 people. If it was up to 6, it would be perfect, but then the first few nights would be way too easy. After 1 play, you can already start formulating strategies for barrier/turret layouts. This game doesn't take long to get good at, and it's got good graphics for what you're paying for it. I bought a 2-pack for $3 and gave one to a friend.All in all, this is a must own for anyone who likes defense games. One tip for when you buy it, try to wait for weapons to go on sale before purchasing them, and you will save a bunch of money in-game that way.I would recommend this game 11 times out of 10."
