,Not Recommended,270550,10622289,"Posted: 21 June, 2014",all,BlasterBox,"Way too repetitive.+Direct and easy game+Players share ammunition+Multiplayer makes it a thousands time more interesting-Waaaay too simple...-Too few weapons-Too few playable characters-Only the host can manage things (buying, selling and placing items)-Doesn't deserve to be paid-There are hackers-There are similar flash games for freePROS1. Direct and easy gameThe game itself is very easy and simple. You know your goal, which is to survive the zombie horde. Having such few and simple tasks makes you keep more focused. Moreover, the controls are extremely easy and it is almost impossible to get lost in the controls.2. Players share ammunitionA fact that adds a lot of realism to the game, playersalwaysshare their ammunition and money earned with each other, trying to survive the zombies. This is an excellent factor that consists that both players have to save ammunition as much as they can, in order to have better weapons sooner. Well, they're in a zombie horde together, they have to share the'wealth', don't they?3. Multiplayer > SoloMultiplayer is a thousand times better than single player. More funny and more challenging. Single player sucks, seriously. The zombies always come in your direction and in a straight line. With multiplayer tasks can be divided (one defends while other fetch ammunition, etc)CONS4. It's too simple!You just defend yourself from zombies. Nothing more. Okay, okay, I understand, this game IS defending yourself from zombies --but, there's literally nothing more! Nothing more! The terrain is flat, there's no boss, there's only one type of ammunition, there are only two or three types of zombies (slow ones and fast ones) and you can only kill a zombie if you shoot it in the head! What the f'ck, seriously~5. Few weaponsThere are just a fw weapons, ten or eleven, I estimate (along with one turret). Some have different aspects from each other but there are not enough weapons! This game's lacking mines, solid walls, homing missiles, katanas, daggers, bows and maybe some buffs? Bruning aura, speed aura, defenses, healing, luring... What about pets that deal a little damage? Or guns upgrades?6. Three playable charactersJust three: one guy, a girl and a SWAT member. They're all the same, the only difference between them is the appearance, nothing more. One could be a bit stronger than other, or faster, maybe more accurate? Or there could be level up system to increase defense for a small amount? But no.7. Only the host does things between waves!Let me explain. Zombies attack in waves. Between those waves the host can buy weapons or barriers, manage the ammunition or disassemble turrets. What about the other players? They just keep looking! Sometimes you want to help, building a nice blockade or buy a different ammunition and you can't, because this game system is bad! Being host means being the king8.This game doesn't deserves to be paidNot even a penny. The game itself is cheap (I bought it for ~R$1.50 -- ~US$0.70, I think) but I recognize I wasted my time, that this game shouldn't even be worth a penny. I bought the two-pack to play it with my cousin but now I realize this game was a waste of money and time (sorry developers!). The whole game looks like it was made in a hurry, to earn money and nothing more. It's so badly made that I played for half an hour and earned about 50% of the game achievements...9. HackersThe game community is dead. Along the dead community hackers usually join you room and eep trolling zombies and killing the rest of the fun and constantly you have to stop waht you're doing and ban them. I don't blame this game for the hackers, but they're annoying.10. There are similar games for free!There are similar flash and unity games likeYet Another Zombie Defensefor free! Some of them areBoxhead series. And even they're simple, they are as fun as YAZD and free of charge!"
