,Not Recommended,270550,15163833,"Posted: 1 April, 2015",all,mohawkd12,"In the very short ammount of time I (thankfully) spent playing this game, I was surprised time and time again - and not by a thrilling storyline or astounding graphics - but by the sheer lack of depth this game offers. Needless to say, I didn't expect much going in, as the title and price surely indicated.But a part of me, maybe niavely, at least expected some basic core elements of a shoot em' up waze-based zombie survival game, such as noise made by either the zombies, my character, or guns. Nope. The best you get is a single monotous thud sound when firing some of the weapons - which sounds less like an actual gunshot, and more like the sound of your heart sinking at the sight of this game.Another basic feature that is missing altogether: a point. Sure, it's called Yet Another Zombie Defense for a reason, and that's exactly what one should expect from it. But the utter lack of depth to the game - besides a handful of guns to buy and a few player upgrades (which are unlocked here and there, but don't provide much difference to the game) leaves you bored after only 5 or 10 minutes.Ultimately, if you buy this *flash game*, here's what you can expect: running in circles in an extremely limited, un detailed environment, shooting identical zombie after ifdentical zombie silently, while a repetative music track from some royalty-free music site plays endlessly. Oh, and keep an eye on your health, because there's no sound or visual indication that you are being hurt, other than the small red bar in the top corner of your screen disappearing with each hit, making you question if you're really playing a game from the 21st century or not.However, I understand the limited capabilities of independent developers, and for that I feel this review may be a bit harsh. But, then again, independent or not, if you want good reviews and happy players, make a decent game.Thankfully, I only payed about $1 for this game, and I do know that you get what you pay for. But, then again, I've played free flash games that are 5+ years old that are easily 100 times better than this garbage. Don't waste your time or money here."
