76561198013728552,Not Recommended,270550,19118759,"Posted: 16 November, 2015",all,Bitch,"When I read all the great reviews on this game, I decided to purchase the 2pack for $2.99.  I hopped in the game and matched up with 2 random players online.  Game was a bit fun for a few rounds.  Then I started to wonder why the graphics would lag when about 25-40 zombies would be dead in the same round.  My pc build could handle crysis 2 on ultra settings and almost any other very high end graphics game on high.  Anyways, i continued to play, and building forts didn't matter anymore because they would go down within the first 15 seconds of a round.  Every round resulted in everyone dieing in the first 20-25 seconds MAX except for myself.. I found myself just running in a circle around the map with a chainsaw and slowly killing the rest of the zombies.  The only challenge was to get the money before it disappeared (for the other players to spend) while having no upgrades on pickup reach/range.  So, basically, 1st game i played of zombie defense and already i was invincible with probably the cheapest weapon buy in game, the chainsaw.  Everyone thought i was hacking but obviously they were just too.. dumb to actually listen to me when i say ""just run around in a circle like i have been every round and you won't die.""  So in conclusion, the idea sounded VERY fun, i've always wanted to play a defense map where you could upgrade either weapons or your character stats and build turrets.  The game however, lags when more than 30 zombies are dead on your screen, weapons are very similar in damage and effect so there's not a lot of interesting/entertaining strategies you could use.  Although there are a nice range of weapons you could buy (but like I said they are all similar so it's not a big difference of buying them).  So, good idea, bad development.Oh and I told my friend that I gifted the 2nd part of the pack to not even waste his time.  This game was not only a waste of even the small amount of $2.99, but a waste of an hour of the very limited game time that I have."
