76561198067920052,Recommended,270550,11137076,"Posted: 8 July, 2014",all,SgtSnyder88,"This game will not change your life, but it is fun and addictingThe entire game centers around a single street lamp at the middle of a very small map. The further you venture from the lamp, the darker it gets. So you are ecnouraged to stay near the lamp but not restricted from straying.It's your standard horde mode in that waves of enemies are sent against you that increase in quantity and difficulty as the game progresses. Killing enemies can net health, money, or ammo drops that disappear over time so you must be somewhat quick in picking them up.In between the waves you have the opporuntity to purchase various weapons and defenses which can give you a great advantage in the next wave. A nice feature is that these items will ocassionally go on sale making them significantly cheaper than their original price and stretching your money further. This can help in giving you that little edge up you need earlier than you would otherwise be able to afford it. Which can seriously help late game.As stated before, this game will not change your life and it isn't without it's faults. Mainly, it's limited. I would really like to see it grow and have new weapons and defenses added, maybe slightly expand the map over time.As is, this game is worth every bit of the few dollars I paid for it and I hope to see more.I'd give it a 3/5"
