76561198105205197,Recommended,270550,11025894,"Posted: 2 July, 2014",all,Captain Facepalm,"Yet Another Zombie Defense is a survival twin stick shooter.Gameplay is pretty straight forward. You try to survive wave after wave of zombies until you finally die.The weapons are typical for a zombie survival game (pistol, shotgun, flamethrower, SMG, Assault rifle, rocket launcher, etc). The map could use a little more detail. It's just a big floor of concrete with a lamppost in the center. (If you add some lines it could be a parking lot. Maybe they could even add some pot holes, and a few abandoned cars.)The game only has three playable characters guy, girl, and swat.The game could also use some more gore. (The zombies just fall over dead after shooting them. Exit wounds and blood splatter effects would make the zombies look sharp.)So far I haven't encountered any bugs.Yet Another Zombie Defense has the potential to be a very good game. At the moment it's an okay game with a blank canvas. Maybe after a few updates this game can really shine."
,Recommended,270550,11058317,"Posted: 3 July, 2014",all,Toby1066,"To call this a game would be a disservice to games in general. Now, hear me out before you dismiss this statement. This is an experience like no other. Playing this game with friends, I truly discovered what it was like to love again. Running around the only light source in the game, desperately running from your pursuers while trying to pick up their leavings, is obviously an analogy for something deeper, something more akin to a spiritual release. As I lasered the lumbering forms of those I can only imagine I used to know, as Night after dreary Night came on, leaving little or no time to reflect on my actions leading up to this, the most drastic of situations, I knew that I had found the true meaning of futility. And when, invariably, I died, leaving my friend to be eaten by those brain-hungry beings that had dogged our footsteps, my only thought was that of retrying, doing better, surviving one more round.A true work of art."
