,Not Recommended,270550,16708120,"Posted: 25 June, 2015",all,pokusan,"Kind of hard to say here, but I ultimately can't recommend it. I got it on sale for $0.75, which I think would be the only time to buy this game. I finished all the achievements in 3 hours and it isn't hard to get any of them. I'll say what's good and not so good about the game quickly.Good:- Online multiplayer + leaderboards: You can actually join any game that is being played up to 4 people and you can choose to let people join your game or to just allow friends, or not allow anyone. It's easier to rack up the achievements with people and get onto the leaderboards.- Quick perfect game & avg. game completion %: There is only 1 achievement that requires a bit of tact and strategy, but as soon as I tried it, I got it pretty easily.- Endless mode: For those of you that are into survival.- Easy to pick up and put down: You get into the game quickly, so you can do it to pass some time and try to see how far you can get.Not so good:- Too easy: There really isn't much difficulty to this at all. A little thought as to how to manipulate the mobs takes you a pretty long way.- Not much to the game: it's a pretty simple game, but I wouldn't call it ""fun."" It's just kind of a mindless game.- Music: Same music all the way through, so it gets stale real fast.Simply put, the game just isn't MUCH fun because it doesn't seem rewarding or frantic. I think they really missed out on the feel of the game, because while zombies are pretty mindless, normally there seems to be some sort of danger. The music misses out on this danger or frantic touch too, so overall, I can't recommend the game. However, if you're looking to raise your perfect games and avg. completion %, this is an easy one to help you with that."
