76561198008369673,Recommended,270550,14529220,"Posted: 18 February, 2015",all,Drecano,"I was considering buying this a while ago, but for some reason didnt bother doing so even though it was, even then at full price, super cheap.But on seeing for sale for so little money, I took the dive and really...I'm glad I did actually.  This, for the little amount of money to get this game, is a good deal.  Its cheap, it's cheerful, will definately kill a couple hours and if you bring in a friend, then you got some fun to be had.Ok its far from perfect, hell I did encounter a bit of a bug/glitch that i had to restart the game and on controller ( which I used ) the aiming is a bit hard, but for the price, you can forgive it.Basically the game is a Tower Defence x Twin Stick Shooter x Survival.  Build your own little fort and defend it as best you can.  Simple right?  well yeah, but its not AS simple as it sounds cus of course things get harder and harder as the levels go on.  You got a decent varierty of weapons and defences at your disposal, ranging from simple wooden fences to electric fencing, pistols to RPGs and a bit more.  A rather neat lil tool is the Auto Turret in which you must mount a weapon you have on your person as the gun.  So you can have an Auto tracking shotgun turret, or flamethrower turret defending your base with you.Granted the game looks bland with the grey floor and single solitary lamp post and yes, I think the game would benefit highly from additional environments and more objects in the environment, so hopefully that can be a thing in this games future.All in all, my advice is if you see this on sale, get it.  I got it for 39p....39p!!!  I can buy chocolate bars more expensive then that and enjoy them less then this game.  Really, what you gotta lose when you spend that little?  100mb of space on your hard drive, thats it.  Grab the game, grab friends, kill zombies. Worth it."
