,Recommended,270550,12610012,"Posted: 24 October, 2014",all,EMDream,"I had a blast playing this game. It is much like ""Crimsonland"" also here on steam. You get to pick from a few types of toons. They do nothing other than change what you look like.A normal guy, normal girl, or a swat officer.  You can only access defense mode at first till you get past level 10. You can then play Endless Mode. In defense mode you fight off waves of zombies making money for each kill and they drop random amounts from 250$-750$ as well. You can place turrents and walls to help you as you progress. The turrents you have you buy a gun and place it on the turrent for it to work. In Endless mode you just fight off an endless wave of zombies trying to stay alive as long as you can simple and yet very fun.I had overall a wonderful time playing although not many people were playing only 5 games were ever found at once for me to join and never a endless mode game. I still had a great time I recommend this game to kill a good 4-7 hours.10/10 Simple Strategy Defense done very, very well!!"
