76561198109762804,Recommended,270550,13540895,"Posted: 23 December, 2014",all,TheRealJHamm,"Let me tell you now that this game is admittedly, fun. I would not go as far as to say that it is thrilling for the single player attempt to survive the outbreak, but because of the cheap pricing (and even the sales on top of that) you can pick this game up for yourself and a few more of your friend-o's to play. Heck, my second go, I jumped in a random game with three other players and it operated well: No Lag and No drop in FPS that I could tell. I will go on to say that the game is CURRENTLY at a state where more could be added, but what lies there is an enjoyable framework of a zombie defense game that can continue to grow with support. One of the coolest things that I received was after my second play through of the game, I recieved a message after shutting the game down that the developers are continuing work on this. They have added an endless mode since my first playthrough and their promise on improving this game makes me want to keep playing.Just give it a try, build your defenses, knock some zombie heads, and Have Fun!"
