,Recommended,270550,14252006,"Posted: 30 January, 2015",all,Valence Eos,this game is better then i thuoght
,Recommended,270550,14252581,"Posted: 30 January, 2015",all,Detroit,"I usually write a review for a game when I play it 10 hours... although as bad as it may sound that I've only played an hour and I'm reviewing, it's actually not that bad in some respects.The gun selection is pretty big, I have to say. It's bigger than some $60 games out there, there is a good variety of guns.Graphics are so/so but the fact that there's one lightpost and then a bunch of open land, there could at least be a little more scenery in my opinion.Trading cards are easy, just the way I like it.No voices in the characters, no running but the zombies increase in difficulty which is a good challenge.Two game modes are actually enough for this game, it keeps you satisfied.Online play works fantastic, probably the game's best feature. Online play makes the game easier and more enjoyable with randoms and friends.For $1.99 and was on sale for 49 cents at one point, It's something you should consider buying.Items like barriers and turrets don't help as much as you would hope, but creating a base around the lightpost (hint, hint) and trapping yourself inside with a turret on each side is a EXTREMELY good idea surprisingly.Achievements, fun to try to accomplish. I have yet to get more but they do increase in difficult, so I like them.I bought this game for my friend and he doesn't play it that much on his own time without friends (me)  so I don't know if he enjoys the single player as much the multiplayer when playing. I do however.I do recommend this game, for $1.99, it's a steal, a good couple hours to get into. A few flaws, but many advantages. No campaign which kinda stinks, but endless night, never stops. No character voices, but tons of screaming zombies. Guns are generic, but there's a lot of them. Barriers and Turrets can be useless at points, until you find the right way to use them. Single-player is good, Multiplayer is excellent. Be the girl, she has smiley faces on her pants. -Detroit0127"
